example.eg: A fallen log blocked the path.
example.egtrans: 一块落下的树干挡住了道路。

example.eg: He grabbed four logs to throw on the fire.
example.egtrans: 他把四块木头投到火里。

trans_examp.trans_cn: 原木, 圆木, 圆木

dsense.name: log
dsense.guideword: (aviation, shipping: trip record) (航海或者飞行)

example.eg: The pilot recorded the flight in her log.
example.egtrans: 飞行员在她的日志中记录了此次飞行。

example.eg: Please use the log to track any changes to the process.
example.egtrans: 请使用日志跟踪对程序的所有变动。

example.eg: The log lists every event.
example.egtrans: 系统日志列出了所有事件。

example.eg: We kept a log of our journeys around the world.
example.egtrans: 我们为自己的环球之旅记录了旅行日志。

trans_examp.trans_cn: 旅行记录, 旅行日志

example.eg: The lumber company has not begun to log yet.
example.egtrans: 木材公司还没有开始伐木。

example.eg: The company is planning to log this forest.
Don't forget to log the flight in the book.

trans_examp.trans_cn: 记录, 把…记录下来, 把…记入日志

example.eg: The athlete logged many hours at practice.
The cycling team logged seventy miles today.

trans_examp.trans_cn: 航行距离达到, 行驶距离达到

example.eg: The men logging the trees wore protective helmets.
You have to log in to view your friends' photos on Facebook.
example.egtrans: 你必须登录才能在Facebook上浏览你朋友的照片。//我必须先登录才能查看我的电子邮件账户。

dsense.name: log into [sth], log onto [sth]
dsense.guideword: (computing: sign into site) (计算机登录网站)

example.eg: To log into the network, you'll need the password.
Log off but don't shut down the computer.
To read this forum, just log onto wordreference.com.
Don't forget to log out of your email when using a shared computer.  I must log out before my mother returns.
example.egtrans: 使用公用电脑时，不要忘记注销您的邮箱。在我妈妈回来之前，我必须注销登录。

trans_examp.trans_cn: 变更日志, 更新日志

example.eg: My grandfather built this log cabin with his own two hands.
The website wouldn't complete the login because Mike misspelled his password.
Kate forgot her login for her email account and had to look it up in her notebook.
We checked the logbook to see when the instrument was last maintained.
The ship's log showed that the ship was heading northeast at the time of the collision.
You were already sleeping like a log when I came to bed.

dsense.name: wood burner, wood-burning stove, log burner

trans_examp.trans_cn: 圣诞柴火, 圣诞节原木
